articles.title: UK and Australia sign new defence pact - DAWN.com
articles.description: The agreement stops short of a full mutual defence pact, which would bind one side to intervene if the other was attacked.
articles.content:
The United Kingdom and Australia inked a new defence agreement in Canberra on Thursday, as they try to boost a fledgling nuclear-powered submarine programme with the United States.
